CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Corporations and Associations – Principal Offices – Private Mailboxes
3 FOR the purpose of authorizing an address supplied by a commercial mail receiving agency
4 to be designated as the principal office of a Maryland corporation, limited liability
5 company, limited liability partnership, or limited partnership, under certain
6 circumstances; providing for the disclosure of certain contact information by a
7 commercial mail receiving agency; and generally relating to the principal offices of
8 corporate entities.
9 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
10 Article – Corporations and Associations
11 Section 1–101(a)
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2025 Replacement Volume)
14 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
15 Article – Corporations and Associations
16 Section 1–101(w)
17 Annotated Code of Maryland
18 (2025 Replacement Volume)
19 BY adding to
20 Article – Corporations and Associations
21 Section 1–407
22 Annotated Code of Maryland
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
