2 HOUSE BILL 308
1 (2025 Replacement Volume)
2 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
3 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
4 Article – Corporations and Associations
5 1–101.
6 (a) In this article, unless the context clearly requires otherwise, the following
7 words have the meanings indicated.
8 (w) “Principal office” means:
9 (1) The place in this State filed or recorded with the Department as the
10 principal office of a Maryland corporation, limited liability company, limited liability
11 partnership, or limited partnership; [or]
12 (2) SUBJECT TO § 1–407 OF THIS TITLE, AN ADDRESS SUPPLIED BY A
13 COMMERCIAL MAIL RECEIVING AGENCY WITH WHICH A MARYLAND CORPORATION,
14 LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY, LIMITED LIABILITY PARTNERSHIP, OR LIMITED
15 PARTNERSHIP HAS A VALID COMMERCIAL MAIL RECEIVING AGREEMENT IN
16 ACCORDANCE WITH U.S. POSTAL SERVICE REGULATIONS; OR
17 (3) If there is no principal office designated UNDER ITEM (1) OF THIS
18 SUBSECTION OR ADDRESS SUPPLIED UNDER ITEM (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, the main
19 office of the Maryland corporation, limited liability company, limited liability partnership,
20 or limited partnership in this State for the transaction of business.
21 1–407.
22 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “COMMERCIAL MAIL RECEIVING AGENCY” MEANS A
23 PERSON THAT IS AUTHORIZED BY THE U.S. POSTAL SERVICE TO ACCEPT THE
24 DELIVERY OF MAIL ON BEHALF OF ANOTHER PERSON AS A BUSINESS SERVICE.
25 (B) IF A PERSON DESIGNATES AN ADDRESS PROVIDED BY A COMMERCIAL
26 MAIL RECEIVING AGENCY AS A PRINCIPAL OFFICE FOR PURPOSES OF THIS ARTICLE,
27 THE PERSON ACKNOWLEDGES THAT THE MAIL RECEIVING AGENCY SHALL PROVIDE
28 THE CONTACT INFORMATION INCLUDED IN USPS FORM 1583 TO THE DEPARTMENT
29 OR A LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENCY ON REQUEST.
30 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
31 October 1, 2026.

